    <p> This time I would like to report on my time in the Yha Railway Square and what went wrong there. </p>
    <p> On my second arrival in Sydney I was more lucky with the hostel I had chosen. I had chosen the Yha Railway Square for two reasons. First, this accommodation is part of the Australian youth hostel association. That means I get a nice discount because I am a member and you can expect a certain minimum level of quality. Second, you get the opportunity to stay in the railway car or in the building. Furthermore, this hostel even has an outdoor pool that I unfortunately never used. Either the weather was stupid or I was busy. </p>
    <p> I had booked the first nights in my sleeping car. It turned out that the cars were separated by glass walls, standing right next to the track 1 of the Sydney Hauptbahnhof and thus actually overnight in the train station;). The hostel solved it super. Nice idea only sometimes made it difficult to fall asleep. </p>
