    <p> So I went out of the door as normal in the morning and thought nothing. Since I had not deposited my cell phone number in the hostel, they couldn't call me and ask why I didn't change. So the hostel opened my value and deposited my valuables at the reception and left me a note that I would like to report. </p>
    <p> Of course you can imagine how mad I was when I found the note. Of course, the reception had simply stuffed all my things in garbage bags. Thus, the toothpaste on the lens of my camera was crushed from the tripod. I didn't even apologize to me, but after it turned out that the error was at the hostel, I at least got a new padlock free of charge because they had destroyed mine to clear out my closet. </p>
    <p> So I was more likely to put it into the room, for a day. In this room I spent the two booked and paid nights and then I was finally able to move into the apartment. </p>

