    <p> During these two weeks I learned a group of Germans with whom I spent my free time. We went out to eat together, for weekly fireworks or cooked together. When cooking, we always found that there was apparently someone in the hostel stealed the food. As good as every day, someone from our team was missing. It was a wide variety of things. Sometimes it was tomatoes, sometimes eggs and even the entire bag with food. I even got away quite lightly. I only got ketschup away. Unfortunately, my iPhone loading edges lost. But I cannot say with certainty whether I lost it on the way from the lounge area to my room or whether someone deliberately stolen it to me. </p>
    <p> I had summarized for two really pleasant weeks in the Yha Railway Square. The quality is right for the really good price. The location is great. The staff is usually friendly and on Wednesdays there is free of charge pancakes for breakfast. I met nice people during time. Mostly Germans. Two boys belonging to this group, I should unexpectedly meet again a few weeks later. But more about that later. </p>

